[Patient] How much water should I drink daily to manage my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for 1.5-2 liters of fluid daily, including water, juice, and soups.
[Patient] Can I drink soda or coffee instead of water?
[Healthcare Educator] Water is best, but limit soda and coffee due to caffeine and sugar content.
[Patient] What about fruits like watermelon or oranges, are they okay?
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, fruits with high water content like watermelon and oranges are good choices.
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake throughout the day?
[Healthcare Educator] Use a measuring cup or water bottle to keep track of how much you drink.